variabili e quali usare :
int = integers(2 o 4 byte, -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647);
char = caratteri (1 byte, 0 a 255);
unsigned int = integer che non puo essere negativo (65,535 or 0 to 4,294,967,295, 2 o 4 byte);
long = in pratica il doppio di int;
short = vabbe';
void = puo starci qualunque cosa;
const char\int\void... = la variabile non puo essere cambiata dopo averla dichiarata.

come compilare un programma :

gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror (nome del file);
./a.out (da solo, oppure seguito da un argomento se usato ac av);
ex:
gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror ft_capitalize_first_word.c
./a.out "tua mamma troia"
output: Tua Mamma Troia.

operatori :

"==" 	Checks if the values of two operands are equal or not. If yes, then the condition becomes true. 	(A == B) is not true.
"!=" 	Checks if the values of two operands are equal or not. If the values are not equal, then the condition becomes true. 	(A != B) is true.
">" 	Checks if the value of left operand is greater than the value of right operand. If yes, then the condition becomes true. 	(A > B) is not true.
"<" 	Checks if the value of left operand is less than the value of right operand. If yes, then the condition becomes true. 	(A < B) is true.
">=" 	Checks if the value of left operand is greater than or equal to the value of right operand. If yes, then the condition becomes true. 	(A >= B) is not true.
"<=" 	Checks if the value of left operand is less than or equal to the value of right operand. If yes, then the condition becomes true. 	(A <= B) is true.

&&  serve a dire letteralmente la parola (e) cioe include.
||  questo vuoldire oppure;
!   da solo vuole vedere se l operazione e falsa.

+ 	Adds two operands. 	A + B = 30
− 	Subtracts second operand from the first. 	A − B = -10
* 	Multiplies both operands. 	A * B = 200
/ 	Divides numerator by de-numerator. 	B / A = 2
% 	Modulus Operator and remainder of after an integer division. 	B % A = 0
++ 	Increment operator increases the integer value by one. 	A++ = 11
-- 	Decrement operator decreases the integer value by one. 	A-- = 9
